## F1 Edu-Racer – Frontend Guidelines & Design System

---

### 1. **Design Principles**

- **Clarity over clutter** – HUD and menus should never overwhelm gameplay.
- **Game-first UI** – Minimal and contextual UI with visual priority on the track and car.
- **Educational cues** – Use tooltips, overlays, and visual feedback tied directly to in-game concepts (like tire temp, fuel, race line).
- **Responsiveness** – Designed for desktops (keyboard-first), but future-friendly for touch adaptations.

---

### 2. **Fonts**

| Purpose            | Font                  | Source                         |
|--------------------|-----------------------|--------------------------------|
| UI & HUD Labels    | **Orbitron**          | [Google Fonts](mdc:https:/fonts.google.com/specimen/Orbitron) |
| Secondary Text     | **Roboto** (fallback) | [Google Fonts](mdc:https:/fonts.google.com/specimen/Roboto)   |
| Lap Time / Digital | **Share Tech Mono**   | [Google Fonts](mdc:https:/fonts.google.com/specimen/Share+Tech+Mono) |

**Usage Suggestions:**
- Use `Orbitron` for menus, buttons, and HUD elements.
- Use `Share Tech Mono` for digital elements (lap time, reaction timer, fuel).
- Use `Roboto` for tooltips, glossary, and tutorial text.

---

### 3. **Color Palette**

| Use Case         | Color        | Hex       | Description |
|------------------|--------------|-----------|-------------|
| Primary Accent   | Red          | `#FF2D00` | Used for start lights, alerts, penalties |
| Secondary Accent | Cyan Blue    | `#00E0FF` | Used for DRS zone, boost, overtake indicators |
| Background Dark  | Charcoal     | `#1A1A1A` | Game background, HUD base |
| Card / Panel     | Asphalt Grey | `#2F2F2F` | Menus, tooltip backdrops |
| Text Light       | White        | `#FFFFFF` | For titles and main text |
| Text Subtle      | Light Grey   | `#B0B0B0` | Secondary text, labels |
| Success/Positive | Green Lime   | `#00FF99` | For perfect starts, achievements |
| Warning          | Yellow       | `#FFCC00` | For tire warnings, pit alerts |
| Error            | Orange/Red   | `#FF5733` | For crashes, fuel low, damage indicators |

---

### 4. **Spacing & Layout Rules**

| Rule                 | Value        | Notes |
|----------------------|--------------|-------|
| Base Unit            | `8px`        | All spacing based on this multiplier (8, 16, 24...) |
| Padding (Buttons)    | `12px 20px`  | Comfortable clickable areas |
| Menu Gutter          | `24px`       | Space between menu items or HUD blocks |
| HUD Margin from Edge | `16px`       | Keeps elements from crowding screen edges |
| Tooltip Max Width    | `300px`      | Prevents long text overflow |

**Grid System:**
- Use a **flexbox-based layout** for menus and HUDs.
- In-game overlays and HUD should anchor to screen edges (top-right, bottom-left etc.) with defined pixel margins.

---

### 5. **Preferred UI Library**

- **Custom UI using Phaser Scenes & RexUI Plugin**  
  - [RexUI Docs](mdc:https:/rexrainbow.github.io/phaser3-rex-notes/docs/site/ui-overview)
  - Allows creation of buttons, sliders, text boxes directly in Phaser.
  - Integrates tightly with game state (e.g., updating HUD from gameplay).

**Why not React or HTML overlay?**
- Phaser UI keeps the game fully in canvas.
- No cross-layer communication issues.
- Easier for animation, placement, and HUD control within the game scene.

---

### 6. **Icon Set**

| Category         | Icon Set        | Source |
|------------------|------------------|--------|
| UI / Menu Icons  | **Phosphor Icons** (SVG) | [https://phosphoricons.com/](mdc:https:/phosphoricons.com) |
| In-Game Indicators | **Custom Sprites** | Designed using GIMP/Figma |
| Status Symbols   | FontAwesome (fallback for web menus) | [https://fontawesome.com](mdc:https:/fontawesome.com) |

**Phosphor** is modern, customizable, and works great with SVGs in canvas or converted to bitmap for performance.

---

### 7. **Example HUD Elements (Guided)**

- **Top Left:** Current Lap / Total Laps  
- **Top Right:** Fuel, Tire Temp, DRS Button  
- **Bottom Center:** Speed / Gear (if added later)  
- **Center-Top:** Reaction Timer (only at race start)  
- **Post-Race:** Modal with sector breakdown, ghost comparison

